results.name: Expansion of Product_{k>0} 1/(1 + x^k)^(k*3).
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
formula: a(n) ~ (-1)^n * exp(-1/4 + 2^(-5/3) * 3^(4/3) * Zeta(3)^(1/3) * n^(2/3)) * A^3 * Zeta(3)^(1/12) / (2^(2/3) * 3^(5/12) * sqrt(Pi) * n^(7/12)), where A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant A074962. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Apr 13 2017
results.author: _Seiichi Manyama_, Apr 11 2017
